textBeforeTable: WBL Football Coldwater picked off Versailles quarterback  Nick Campbell three times. Coldwater is tied atop the MAC standings with Marion Local and Delphos St. John’s at 3-0.   Siefring ended the game with three catches for 71 yards. Coldwater rallied from a 19-7 third-quarter deficit with two Caleb Siefring touchdown receptions and two Austin Bruns touchdown runs as the Cavaliers scored 29 unanswered points in the second half. Coldwater 36, Versailles 19 Bath 37, Van Wert 8 Bath snapped a two-game skid with a win over the Cougars. Van Wert slumped to 0-5, 0-4 in the WBL. Elida 35, Shawnee 7 Elida quarterback Reggie McAdams went 13-of-21 for 247 yards with two touchdowns in the Bulldogs’ blow out win over the Indians. Both teams threw three interceptions. Kenton moves to 4-0 in the WBL, tied atop the league standings with unbeaten Wapakoneta. O-G running back Tristan Parker rushed for 117 yards and a score on 23 carries. Kenton senior quarterback Maty Mauk threw for 212 yards and two touchdowns and rushed for 179 yards and three touchdowns to lead the Wildcats to a 36-20 win over the Titans.
